page.title: 11ECOLOGY
page.content: Disused Railway Line-Part of abandoned line from Northampton-Market Harborough closed 1960.Sold to - Nothampton Steam Railway Society. They have bought a locomotive and two coaches and hope,when repaired, to use them for Week end pleasure travel. We walked along the line for 1 km until we came to a fence.We climbed it and looked for signs of wild life.We saw 14 different animals,birds and insects. We turned round and went back along our measured Km collecting plants.We found 20 different ones.When we got back to school we classified them. The railway track was rusty and some of it was ripped up.
